It is difficult for me to see what is happening here, because the diff refers to `gio/trunc` instead of `master`. Do you know how to change this using git or github interface?

@joelriou I have updated the base branch to `master`.

You can also always view a diff against a different branch by visiting the following url, where in this case `gio/trunc` is the base branch and `gio/trunc-dual-defs` is the head branch:
```
https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/compare/gio/trunc...gio/trunc-dual-defs
```
Closing as this has been incorporated into #20668 (fast-forwarded).

This could be directly the definition of `Truncated.Path` for `X` `n+1`-truncated. Then, there would be no need to have both `Truncated.Path₁` and `Truncated.Path`. Finally, `SSet.Path` can be defined as `Truncated.Path` of the `1`-truncation. This would make two definitions instead of three.

My concern with completely removing `Truncated.Path₁` is that, for `X : SSet.Truncated (n + 1)` , a path in `X` is no longer comparable with a path taken in the further `m + 1` truncation of `X`, as shown below.

What do you think of keeping `Truncated.Path₁` as an auxiliary definition, but defining everything else only on `Truncated.Path` to cut down on the duplication of lemmas and definitions?

```lean
@[ext]
structure Path {n : ℕ} (X : SSet.Truncated.{u} (n + 1)) (m : ℕ) where
  vertex : Fin (m + 1) → ((trunc (n + 1) 0).obj X) _[0]₀
  arrow : Fin m → ((trunc (n + 1) 1).obj X) _[1]₁
  arrow_src (i : Fin m) : X.map (tr (δ 1)).op (arrow i) = vertex i.castSucc
  arrow_tgt (i : Fin m) : X.map (tr (δ 0)).op (arrow i) = vertex i.succ

variable (X : SSet.Truncated 3) (f : Path X 1) (g : Path ((trunc 3 2).obj X) 1)

/--
error: type mismatch
  g
has type
  ((trunc 3 2 ⋯).obj X).Path 1 : Type ?u.8945
but is expected to have type
  X.Path 1 : Type ?u.8945
-/
#guard_msgs in #check f = g
```

For comparison, the following is what I had in mind (with `interval`, `map`, etc. defined only on `Truncated.Path`).

```lean
@[ext]
structure Path₁ (X : SSet.Truncated.{u} 1) (n : ℕ) where
  vertex : Fin (n + 1) → X _[0]₁
  arrow : Fin n → X _[1]₁
  arrow_src (i : Fin n) : X.map (tr (δ 1)).op (arrow i) = vertex i.castSucc
  arrow_tgt (i : Fin n) : X.map (tr (δ 0)).op (arrow i) = vertex i.succ

/-- A path of length `m` in an `n + 1`-truncated simplicial set `X` is given by
the data of a `Path₁` structure on the further 1-truncation of `X`. -/
def Path {n : ℕ} (X : SSet.Truncated.{u} (n + 1)) (m : ℕ) :=
  trunc (n + 1) 1 |>.obj X |>.Path₁ m

variable (X : SSet.Truncated 3) (f : Path X 1) (g : Path ((trunc 3 2).obj X) 1)

/-- info: f = g : Prop -/
#guard_msgs in #check f = g
```
#20668 should now reflect my suggestion above. Please let me know if you see a better way forward.
